@page "/extra"
@namespace DocSiteChromeOverridesExample.Components

@* A plain routed Razor component that sits next to Program.cs. The only
   reason it resolves under DocSite's router is because
   SiteChromeOverrides.BuildAdditionalRoutingAssemblies returns this
   project's assembly, which DocSiteOptions.AdditionalRoutingAssemblies
   then feeds into the router. Remove that seam and /extra 404s. *@

<PageTitle>Extra Page</PageTitle>

<article class="prose mx-auto py-12">
    <h1>Extra Page</h1>
    <p>
        This route lives in a Razor component inside the example's own
        assembly. <code>DocSiteOptions.AdditionalRoutingAssemblies</code>
        widens the DocSite router to cover it.
    </p>
</article>
